{"build_type":"executable","description":"Measurement spike for the token-optimization decision: argv[1]=function name, stdin=IPM package. Emits {function, payload_bytes, skeleton_bytes, rows} where payload_bytes = minified-JSON length of the requested function's full AST (what op.read returns as payload), skeleton_bytes = minified-JSON length of the WHOLE-package bodyless skeleton (what op.map/the map register returns), rows = number of functions in the package. Purpose: quantify where the response bytes actually are (AST payload vs uniform skeleton list) so optimization effort goes to the real sink (elision) rather than the researcher's headline (tabular), and so a tabular win can be measured not assumed. Reuses render_document_value_producing_cstring, compute_string_length_by_scanning, summarize_function_members_into_skeleton, finalize_reader_response_envelope.","module_name":"measure-reader-payload-octet-sizes","package_name":"measure-reader-payload-octet-sizes","function_definitions":{"measure-reader-payload-octet-sizes":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"__argc","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"__argv","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"s_fd","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"function_definitions"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"s_function","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"function"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"s_payload_bytes","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"payload_bytes"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"s_skeleton_bytes","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"skeleton_bytes"}